        "tokensAfter": 21501,
        "summary": "## Goal\nBuild and maintain the Agent Chat web app with 10 agent panels (2-col x 5-row grid), full Telegram sync, instant sorting, typing indicators, and iPhone accessibility via Tailscale. Currently debugging why app works on localhost but shows blank/dark screen on iPhone/Mac browsers.\n\n## Constraints & Preferences\n- Keep 2-col x 5-row grid format (panels ~400-500px tall)\n- Most recent contacted agent at top-left (optimistic, instant, user-initiated only)\n- Fit on iPhone (no cut-off, centered, keyboard above input)\n- Full convos persist on refresh (no message loss, chronological order)\n- Batch updates, tell Bobby before/after work\n- Unread agents move to top (blue pulse dot + glowing panel)\n- Gear ⚙️ shows while agent working (until full response sent, no arbitrary timeout)\n- Enter adds new line; send only on button tap\n- **Separate ports for separate apps**: MC (8787), Agent Chat (8788), Recipe Rip (8789)\n\n## Progress\n### Done\n- [x] MVP built (10 panels, fire-and-forget messaging, 1.2s polling, localStorage v3)\n- [x] Fixed Mac page jumping (textarea focus, no window.scrollTo)\n- [x] Fixed instant agent sorting (tick state, CSS order for stable DOM)\n- [x] Fixed scroll reset (loadedRef, isAtBottomRef, requestAnimationFrame)\n- [x] Fixed iPhone zoom (viewport meta)\n- [x] Fixed iPhone cut-off (minmax(0,1fr) columns, minWidth:0)\n- [x] Fixed localStorage race/batching (messagesRef, syncToStorage before setMessages)\n- [x] Fixed quota exceeded (prune to 100 recent msgs/agent)\n- [x] Fixed keyboard visibility (scroll panel to bottom on focus/tap)\n- [x] CSS included in prod build (import './index.css' in main.tsx)\n- [x] Custom Express proxy server (server.cjs port 8787, static + /tools proxy)\n- [x] Unread notifications (blue pulsing dot next to name, panel glow/border pulse)\n- [x] Auto-expand textarea (grows to 120px, collapses on send)\n- [x] Keyboard dismiss on send (blur + document.activeElement.blur)\n- [x] Scroll lock (tap panel to enable scroll, inactive panels pass to grid)\n- [x] Gear emoji ⚙️ in header for typing/working (no timeout - shows until agent done)\n- [x] Context persistence across refresh (getLastSentTs/setLastSentTs for maxTsRef)\n- [x] Duplicate fix (pendingTexts ref, text-based dedupe 30s window)\n- [x] Sorting on user sends only (removed from polling)\n- [x] Enter adds new line (removed onKeyDown handler)\n- [x] Panel highlight on select (agent color glow/border, deselect on grid tap)\n- [x] Deselect on tap outside (grid onTouchEnd, panel onTouchEnd)\n- [x] Removed service worker code from index.html (was caching old builds)\n- [x] **App confirmed working on localhost** (screenshot shows all 10 agents: Dean, Emmy, Finn, X, YoYo, Rex, Cody, DJ, TT, Reese)\n- [x] Gateway restarted - API endpoints working (/api/bills, /api/habits, /api/money)\n- [x] Created separate Vite entry points (index.html → main.tsx for MC, agent.html → main-agent.tsx for Agent Chat)\n- [x] Vite build produces separate chunks: main-Cifg6Hl3.js (99KB), AgentChatApp-DOk_bsXq.js (203KB), agent-59oiFu0-.js (0.15KB)\n- [x] Created serve-apps.cjs to serve different HTML files on different ports (8787 → index.html, 8788 → agent.html)\n- [x] serve-apps.cjs proxies /tools to gateway:18789 and /api to 3001\n- [x] All servers confirmed running: API (3001), MC (8787), Agent Chat (8788), Vite (8790)\n- [x] Subagent tasks completed successfully\n\n### In Progress\n- [ ] **Debug browser blank screen on Bobby's devices**: App works on localhost (30819 chars in root) but shows blank/dark screen on iPhone/Mac\n- [ ] **Clear browser cache issue**: Browser still loading cached old bundle (index-WZABLW1v.js) instead of new chunks\n\n## Key Decisions\n- **Separate entry points via Vite**: Created index.html (main.tsx router) and agent.html (main-agent.tsx direct AgentChatApp) for separate builds\n- **Multi-port server (serve-apps.cjs)**: Serves different entry points on different ports to avoid hash routing confusion\n- **Proxy setup**: serve-apps.cjs forwards /tools to gateway:18789 and /api to 3001\n- **localhost works, client browsers don't**: App renders correctly on localhost (screenshot confirmed), issue is browser cache on client devices\n- **Kill & restart pattern**: Used `lsof -ti :port | xargs kill -9` to free ports when servers conflict\n- **Git reset broke it**: Bobby reset to origin/main which overwrote AgentChatApp - had to restore to f9acbfb which has AgentChatApp code\n\n## Next Steps\n1. **Cache clearing for Bobby**: Instruct him to clear Safari cache on both iPhone and Mac\n2. **Terminal command for Mac**: `killall Safari && open -a Safari \"http://localhost:8788/\"` to force fresh load\n3. **Chrome with no cache**: `open -a \"Google Chrome\" --args --disk-cache-size=0 \"http://localhost:8788/\"`\n4. **Verify Agent Chat on Tailscale**: After cache clear, test http://100.103.22.35:8788/ on iPhone\n\n## Critical Context\n- **Working URLs**:\n  - localhost:8787 → Mission Control (via main.tsx router)\n  - localhost:8788 → Agent Chat (direct, no hash needed)\n  - Tailscale: http://100.103.22.35:8788/ → Agent Chat\n- **Key files**: \n  - ~/agent-mission-control/src/main.tsx (MC router)\n  - ~/agent-mission-control/src/main-agent.tsx (Agent Chat direct render)\n  - ~/agent-mission-control/agent.html (Agent Chat entry point)\n  - ~/agent-mission-control/serve-apps.cjs (multi-port server)\n  - ~/agent-mission-control/server/mission-control-api.cjs (API on port 3001)\n- **Bundle chunks**: main-Cifg6Hl3.js, AgentChatApp-DOk_bsXq.js, agent-59oiFu0-.js\n- **LocalStorage keys**: 'agent_chat_v3' (messages), 'agent_last_contacted' (sorting), 'agent_last_read', 'agent_last_reply', 'agent_last_sent'\n- **Gateway port**: 18789 (/tools/invoke)\n- **API server port**: 3001 (/api/bills, /api/habits, /api/money)\n- **Bobby's iPhone Tailscale IP**: 100.87.202.117\n- **Mac Tailscale IP**: 100.103.22.35\n- **Root div empty cause**: Old cached bundle (index-WZABLW1v.js) still loading in browser despite server serving new files\n\n---\n\n**Turn Context (split turn):**\n\n\n\n## Original Request\nUser reported that localhost:8788 is bringing up Mission Control instead of Agent Chat when they expected to see the agent chat interface.\n\n## Early Progress\n- Assistant examined AgentChatApp.tsx source code to understand what it renders (10 agent panels: Dean, Emmy, Finn, X, YoYo, Rex, Cody, DJ, TT, Reese)\n- Assistant took a screenshot of port 8788 which showed agent chat with both widgets AND agent panels\n- Assistant hypothesized that the Agent Chat app includes Mission Control widgets mixed with agent panels\n- Attempted to navigate to port 8787 to take a comparison screenshot\n\n## Context for Suffix\n- Assistant opened a new browser tab for localhost:8787 (Mission Control) and was about to take a screenshot to compare the two apps side-by-side\n- Suffix shows a screenshot being taken from the Mission Control tab to help visually differentiate the two apps for the user\n\n<read-files>\n/Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/skills/lobstalk/SKILL.md\n/Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/workspace-cody/memory/2026-04-05.md\n/Users/bobbygalletta/agent-mission-control/prod-server.cjs\n/Users/bobbygalletta/agent-mission-control/src/App.tsx\n/Users/bobbygalletta/agent-mission-control/src/index.css\n/opt/homebrew/lib/node_modules/openclaw/skills/node-connect/SKILL.md\n/opt/homebrew/lib/node_modules/openclaw/skills/skill-creator/SKILL.md\n</read-files>\n\n<modified-files>\n/Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/workspace-cody/memory/2026-04-06.md\n/Users/bobbygalletta/agent-mission-control/dist/test-module.html\n/Users/bobbygalletta/agent-mission-control/dist/test-react.html\n/Users/bobbygalletta/agent-mission-control/dist/test.html\n/Users/bobbygalletta/agent-mission-control/index.html\n/Users/bobbygalletta/agent-mission-control/proxy-server.js\n/Users/bobbygalletta/agent-mission-control/serve-apps.cjs\n/Users/bobbygalletta/agent-mission-control/server-https.js\n/Users/bobbyga