        "summary": "## Goal\nBuild and maintain the Agent Chat web app with 10 agent panels (2-col x 5-row grid), full Telegram sync, instant sorting, typing indicators, and iPhone accessibility via Tailscale. Add cross-device sync (Mac ↔ iPhone) so the same state is always shown on both devices.\n\n## Constraints & Preferences\n- Keep 2-col x 5-row grid format (panels ~400-500px tall)\n- Most recent contacted agent at top-left (optimistic, instant, user-initiated only)\n- Fit on iPhone (no cut-off, centered, keyboard above input)\n- Full convos persist on refresh (no message loss, chronological order)\n- **Unread agents move to top** (blue pulse border + glowing panel)\n- **Gear ⚙️ shows while agent working** (debounce: stays until agent silent for 3 seconds)\n- Enter adds new line; send only on button tap\n- **Separate ports for separate apps**: MC (8787), Agent Chat (8788), Recipe Rip (8789)\n- **Cross-device sync**: visible agents, unread state synced between Mac and iPhone via Telegram session storage\n- Tap panel to enable scroll (scroll locked by default)\n- Auto-expand textarea as you type (up to 120px)\n\n## Progress\n### Done\n- [x] MVP built (10 panels, fire-and-forget messaging, 1.2s polling, localStorage v3)\n- [x] Fixed Mac page jumping (textarea focus, no window.scrollTo)\n- [x] Fixed instant agent sorting (tick state, CSS order for stable DOM)\n- [x] Fixed scroll reset (loadedRef, isAtBottomRef, requestAnimationFrame)\n- [x] Fixed iPhone zoom (viewport meta)\n- [x] Fixed iPhone cut-off (minmax(0,1fr) columns, minWidth:0)\n- [x] Fixed localStorage race/batching (messagesRef, syncToStorage before setMessages)\n- [x] Fixed quota exceeded (prune to 100 recent msgs/agent)\n- [x] Fixed keyboard visibility (scroll panel to bottom on focus/tap)\n- [x] CSS included in prod build (import './index.css' in main.tsx)\n- [x] Custom Express proxy server (server.cjs port 8787, static + /tools proxy)\n- [x] Unread notifications (blue pulsing border around panel + blue dot in header)\n- [x] Auto-expand textarea (grows to 120px, collapses on send)\n- [x] Scroll lock (tap panel to enable scroll, inactive panels pass to grid)\n- [x] Context persistence across refresh (history ref per-agent from localStorage)\n- [x] Removed service worker code from index.html (was caching old builds)\n- [x] Created separate Vite entry points (index.html → main.tsx for MC, agent.html → main-agent.tsx for Agent Chat)\n- [x] Vite build produces separate chunks\n- [x] Created serve-apps.cjs to serve different HTML files on different ports (8787 → index.html, 8788 → agent.html, 8789 → recipe-rip)\n- [x] serve-apps.cjs proxies /tools to gateway:18789 and /api to 3001\n- [x] Removed CSP header from serve-apps.cjs (was causing \"CSP blocks eval\" error)\n- [x] **Fixed blank screen bug**: `history` useRef was accidentally deleted in commit `6b3a673` — added back `const history = useRef<Record<string, Message[]>>(loadHistory())` at top of AgentPanel()\n- [x] **Fixed TypeScript build failures**: `history.current` references required the `history` ref declaration\n- [x] **Pushed all 3 apps to GitHub**: 61 commits, committed after every change\n- [x] **iOS scroll-without-tap**: added `touch-action: pan-y pinch-zoom` then reverted (tap-first was desired)\n- [x] **iOS scroll lock**: added `scrollLocked` state + `overflow-y: hidden/auto` toggle — scroll locked by default, tap panel to unlock\n- [x] **Auto-deselect on mouseLeave**: `onMouseLeave` handler on panel clears focus and scroll lock\n- [x] **Header refresh button**: click \"Agent Chat\" header → `window.location.reload()`\n- [x] **Blue pulse unread border**: `panel-unread` CSS class with `@keyframes unread-pulse` (blue glow, 2s cycle), applied via `agent-panel-unread` class on panel div\n- [x] **Manual mark-unread button**: `○` button in panel header, `setUnread(true)` + `setUnreadAgent(agent.id, true)`\n- [x] **Persist unread state**: `getUnreadAgents()` / `setUnreadAgent()` using localStorage key `agent_unread`\n- [x] **Persist visible agents**: `getVisibleAgents()` / `setVisibleAgents()` using localStorage key `agent_visible`\n- [x] **Typing indicator debounce**: 3-second timer resets on every new assistant message — typing stays until agent silent for 3s\n- [x] **Settings menu**: ⚙️ gear button in header, dropdown with checkbox list of all 10 agents, \"Show All\" / \"Hide All\" buttons, `hiddenCount` label in header, grid uses `grid-template-rows: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(400px, 1fr))` for compression\n- [x] **Blue pulse when panel selected**: removed `!focused` condition — blue pulse always triggers on new message, clears on typing (`onInput` handler) or clicking\n- [x] **Textarea auto-expand**: `onChange` auto-grows textarea up to 120px using scrollHeight; resets to 'auto' on send\n\n### In Progress\n- [ ] **Cross-device sync (Mac ↔ iPhone)**: sync `agent_visible` and `agent_unread` via Telegram session storage (gateway API)\n\n### Blocked\n- None\n\n## Key Decisions\n- **`history` ref is critical**: Must be declared as `useRef` at top of `AgentPanel()` — holds all agents' message history from localStorage, shared across renders\n- **Counter-based typing failed**: Agent sending 3 messages in one poll batch caused counter to go 1-3=-2→0 immediately\n- **Debounce approach for typing**: Timer resets on every new assistant message. Typing clears 3s after agent goes silent. Matches Telegram behavior exactly\n- **Blue pulse always shows on new message**: Removed `!focused` condition — blue pulse is independent of focus state, clears on typing or clicking\n- **Visible agents via localStorage**: Settings menu toggles agent visibility, persisted to `agent_visible` key\n- **Grid compression**: `grid-template-rows: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(400px, 1fr))` — hidden agents compress the grid naturally\n- **Separate Vite entries**: `index.html` (MC router) and `agent.html` (direct AgentChatApp) avoid hash routing confusion\n- **Serve-apps.cjs multi-port**: Single server handles 3 apps on different ports with appropriate proxies\n- **git push \"Everything up-to-date\"**: This output appears when local and remote are already in sync — push succeeded\n\n## Next Steps\n1. **Implement cross-device sync**: Store `agent_visible` and `agent_unread` in a shared Telegram session message. Both Mac and iPhone read/write the same message via `gatewayFetch` calls. Use a dedicated session or the shared `agent:main:telegram:direct:BOBBY_ID` session to store the JSON state object.\n2. **Bobby to test typing debounce**: Send a message to an agent and confirm typing stays until 3s after last response\n3. **Bobby to test blue pulse**: Confirm blue pulse appears even when panel is selected, clears when typing starts\n\n## Critical Context\n- **Working URLs**: localhost:8787 (MC), localhost:8788 (Agent Chat), localhost:8789 (Recipe Rip)\n- **Tailscale IP**: http://100.103.22.35:8787/, :8788/, :8789/\n- **Gateway port**: 18789 (/tools/invoke)\n- **API server port**: 3001\n- **Key files**:\n  - `~/agent-mission-control/src/pages/AgentChatApp.tsx` — main component (~625 lines)\n  - `~/agent-mission-control/serve-apps.cjs` — multi-port server\n  - `~/agent-mission-control/agent.html` — Agent Chat entry point\n  - `~/agent-mission-control/server/mission-control-api.cjs` — API on port 3001\n- **LocalStorage keys**: `agent_chat_v3` (messages), `agent_last_contacted` (sorting), `agent_unread` (unread state), `agent_visible` (visible agents)\n- **Git**: origin/main, 61 commits ahead, committed after every change, xAI API key replaced with `${process.env.XAI_API_KEY}`\n- **Recent commits**: `97023a3` (blue pulse when selected), `1d40c60` (debounce typing), `bcde41d` (typing counter), `cef5543` (settings menu), `155410e` (textarea expand)\n- **CSS injected via `<style>` tag**: CSS from template literals in JSX is bundled into the JS file and injected at runtime — not extracted to separate CSS file\n\n---\n\n**Turn Context (split turn):**\n\n\n\n## Original Request\nUser confirmed everything should sync between Mac and iPhone, including typing and blue pulse indicators.\n\n## Early Progress\n- Identified four state elements needing sync: unread (`agent_unread`), visible agents (`agent_visible`), blue pulse, and typing indicator\n- Planned to use gateway's `sessions_updateMetadata` for session-scoped key-value storage\n- Began checking gateway tools availability via `gatewayFetch` calls\n- Discovered `sessions_history`, `sessions_send`, and `sessions_list` are available, but `sessions_updateMetadata` and `sessions_getMetadata` are not\n\n## Context for Suffix\n- The suffix shows attempts to find an alternative way to store/sync cross-device session metadata since `sessions_updateMetadata` is unavailable\n- Still need to resolve how to implement unread and visible agent sync without the missing metadata tools\n- Typing indicator sync via Telegram's native mechanism remains to be verified\n\n<read-files>\n/Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/skills/lobstalk/SKILL.md\n/Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/workspace-cody/memory/2026-04-05.md\n/Users/bobbygalletta/agent-mission-control/dist/agent.html\n/Users/bobbygalletta/agent-mission-control/prod-server.cjs\n/Users/bobbygalletta/agent-mission-control/src/App.tsx\n/Users/bobbygalletta/agent-mission-control/src/index.css\n/opt/homebrew/lib/node_modules/openclaw/skills/node-connect/SKILL.md\n/opt/homebrew/lib/node_modules/openclaw/skills/skill-creator/SKILL.md\n</read-files>\n\n<modified-files>\n/Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/workspace-cody/memory/2026-04-06.md\n/Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/workspace-cody/memory/2026-04-08.md\n/Users/bobbygalletta/agent-mission-control/dist/debug.html\n/Users/bobbygalletta/agent-mission-control/dist/test-module.html\n/Users/bobbygalletta/agent-mission-control/dist/test-page.html\n/Users/bobbygalletta/agent-mission-control/dist/test-react.html\n/Users/bobbygalletta/agent-mission-control/dist/test.html\n/Users/bobbygalletta/agent-mission-control/index.html\n/Users/bobb