        "summary": "## Goal\nBuild and maintain the Agent Chat web app with 10 agent panels (2-col x 5-row grid), full Telegram sync, instant sorting, typing indicators, and iPhone accessibility via Tailscale. Maintain Recipe Rip with a polished, fun loading animation and reliable recipe extraction. Optimize Recipe Rip UI/UX based on user testing and psychology research.\n\n## Constraints & Preferences\n- Keep 2-col x 5-row grid format (panels ~400-500px tall)\n- Most recent contacted agent at top-left (optimistic, instant, user-initiated only)\n- Fit on iPhone (no cut-off, centered, keyboard above input)\n- Full convos persist on refresh (no message loss, chronological order)\n- **Unread agents move to top** (blue pulse border + glowing panel)\n- **Gear ⚙️ shows while agent working** (debounce: stays until agent silent for 3 seconds)\n- Enter adds new line; send only on button tap\n- **Separate ports for separate apps**: MC (8787), Agent Chat (8788), Recipe Rip (8789)\n- **Mac scroll behavior**: scroll anywhere goes to grid by default; click panel first to enable panel scrolling\n- **iOS scroll behavior**: scroll anywhere goes to grid; tap panel first to enable panel scrolling\n- Auto-expand textarea as you type (up to 120px)\n- Recipe Rip: fun food emoji burst on loading screen — DVD screensaver bouncing style, canvas-rendered emojis for crisp iOS display, frosted glass panel, emoji burst reveal animation\n- All Recipe Rip UI copy must be plain language (use \"link\" not \"URL\")\n- Recipe Rip excluded from main git repo (separate repo structure)\n\n## Progress\n### Done\n- [x] MVP built (10 panels, fire-and-forget messaging, 1.2s polling, localStorage v3)\n- [x] Fixed Mac page jumping (textarea focus, no window.scrollTo)\n- [x] Fixed instant agent sorting (tick state, CSS order for stable DOM)\n- [x] Fixed scroll reset (loadedRef, isAtBottomRef, requestAnimationFrame)\n- [x] Fixed iPhone zoom (viewport meta)\n- [x] Fixed iPhone cut-off (minmax(0,1fr) columns, minWidth:0)\n- [x] Fixed localStorage race/batching (messagesRef, syncToStorage before setMessages)\n- [x] Fixed quota exceeded (prune to 100 recent msgs/agent)\n- [x] Fixed keyboard visibility (scroll panel to bottom on focus/tap)\n- [x] CSS included in prod build (import './index.css' in main.tsx)\n- [x] Custom Express proxy server (server.cjs port 8787, static + /tools proxy)\n- [x] Unread notifications (blue pulsing border around panel + blue dot in header)\n- [x] Auto-expand textarea (grows to 120px, collapses on send)\n- [x] Context persistence across refresh (history ref per-agent from localStorage)\n- [x] Created separate Vite entry points (index.html → main.tsx for MC, agent.html → main-agent.tsx for Agent Chat)\n- [x] Created serve-apps.cjs to serve different HTML files on different ports (8787 → index.html, 8788 → agent.html, 8789 → recipe-rip)\n- [x] serve-apps.cjs proxies /tools to gateway:18789 and /api to 3001\n- [x] **Fixed blank screen bug**: `history` useRef was accidentally deleted — added back\n- [x] **Fixed TypeScript build failures**: `history.current` references required the `history` ref declaration\n- [x] **Pushed all 3 apps to GitHub**: committed after every change\n- [x] **iOS scroll lock**: added `scrollLocked` state + `overflow-y: hidden/auto` toggle — scroll locked by default, tap panel to unlock\n- [x] **Auto-deselect on mouseLeave**: `onMouseLeave` handler on panel clears focus and scroll lock\n- [x] **Header refresh button**: click \"Agent Chat\" header → `window.location.reload()`\n- [x] **Blue pulse unread border**: `panel-unread` CSS class with `@keyframes unread-pulse` (blue glow, 2s cycle), applied via `agent-panel-unread` class on panel div\n- [x] **Manual mark-unread button**: `○` button in panel header, `setUnread(true)` + `setUnreadAgent(agent.id, true)`\n- [x] **Persist unread state**: `getUnreadAgents()` / `setUnreadAgent()` using localStorage key `agent_unread`\n- [x] **Persist visible agents**: `getVisibleAgents()` / `setVisibleAgents()` using localStorage key `agent_visible`\n- [x] **Typing indicator debounce**: 3-second timer resets on every new assistant message — typing stays until agent silent for 3s\n- [x] **Settings menu**: ⚙️ gear button in header, dropdown with checkbox list of all 10 agents, \"Show All\" / \"Hide All\" buttons, `hiddenCount` label in header\n- [x] **Textarea auto-expand**: `onChange` auto-grows textarea up to 120px using scrollHeight; resets to 'auto' on send\n- [x] **Removed cross-device sync via Telegram sessions** — agents were receiving AGENT_STATE messages and responding\n- [x] **Removed scroll lock CSS** — grid and chats scroll independently on iOS\n- [x] **Mac wheel scroll**: `onWheel` handler on panel div with `e.preventDefault()` + `e.stopPropagation()` when panel is not focused — scroll goes to grid by default, click panel first to enable panel scroll\n- [x] **iOS touch scroll**: `onTouchMove` handler with `e.stopPropagation()` on panel div — prevents iOS from treating panel as scrollable, lets grid handle all pan gestures\n- [x] **Fixed scroll reset on reorder**: removed `useEffect` that reset `grid.scrollTop = 0` on every tick/re-render; also removed CSS `order` from grid items — array sort now controls DOM order directly\n- [x] **Scroll to bottom on refresh**: `requestAnimationFrame` in initial load `useEffect` now actually scrolls to `scrollHeight`\n- [x] **Duplicate message dedupe**: `processedIdsRef` Set tracks all seen message IDs; checked before adding any message from poll\n- [x] **xAI API key updated**: `xai-xMPUmMTwzAKdvKL6mNm0AkufZ9ZOoeOADhg5f9OCJtQIypMRPP1fogrhmedjLkuwSIONlm9U3jAXq5mB` confirmed working on `api.x.ai/v1/responses`\n- [x] **Launchd agent setup**: Created `com.bobby.mc-all.plist` launchd agent to auto-start `serve-apps.cjs` with XAI_API_KEY env var\n- [x] **Servers auto-restart**: launchd `KeepAlive` keeps `serve-apps.cjs` running (PID auto-restart on crash)\n- [x] **Cross-device state sync abandoned**: Bobby accepted that messages sync via Telegram polling (1.2s); blue pulse and visible agents remain local-only per device\n- [x] **iOS emoji rendering fix**: Canvas-based emoji rendering (72px canvas at 2x resolution, displayed at 36px) completely bypasses iOS's emoji font styling that causes orange outlines/borders\n- [x] **Recipe Rip loading screen fully implemented**:\n  - Frosted glass panel (iOS 26 style blur, rgba(255,255,255,0.15), backdrop-filter:blur(12px))\n  - Orange pulsing border (#FF6B35, @keyframes panel-pulse, 2s ease-in-out infinite)\n  - 143 food/kitchen/culinary emoji items (no duplicates, shuffled pool with sequential draw)\n  - Emojis bounce below header line (y > 100px boundary)\n  - Canvas rendering for crisp emoji on iOS\n  - Glass panel centered at top:35% of viewport\n  - Black text inside glass panel\n  - Demo mode at `?demo=1` for preview without Grok tokens\n- [x] **Emoji burst reveal animation**:\n  - Glass panel shrinks (scale(0), 0.8s cubic-bezier bounce)\n  - Emojis burst outward in all directions (each emoji shoots away from center using atan2 angle + random distance, @keyframes emoji-burst 0.7s ease-out)\n  - Recipe fades in sliding up from below (@keyframes recipe-fadein, 1.2s ease-out, 0.3s delay)\n  - stopBurst() called AFTER animations start (not before) to preserve emoji elements during animation\n  - Recipe shows 600ms after burst starts (overlapping with emoji animation)\n- [x] **Tap logo to refresh**: One tap on \"Recipe Rip\" header logo calls `window.location.reload()`\n- [x] **Placeholder text**: \"Paste Recipe Link Here\" (lowercase \"link\" not \"URL\" for user-friendliness)\n- [x] **Emotion burst timing tuned**: Glass panel transition 0.8s, emoji burst 0.7s, recipe fade-in 1.2s starting at 600ms\n- [x] **Back button padding**: Added left padding (16px 20px) to move it away from left edge\n- [x] **Recipe Rip storage**: localStorage key `recipe_rip_v4` — completely local, no server, persists on iPhone browser\n- [x] **Rex's psychology research on Recipe Rip**: Saved at ~/Desktop/SecondBrain/Projects/RecipeApp/PSYCHOLOGY_RESEARCH.md — covers color palette (#FF6B35 coral orange), UX principles (skeleton screens, one task per screen, 3 tabs max), empty state copy, speed perception, pricing tiers\n- [x] **Recipe Rip sent to Emmy for UX feedback** (via agent-message.sh)\n- [x] **AllRecipe Rip emoji items are purely culinary**: 143 items — main food, bakery/sweets, beverages, cooking/chef, utensils, serving dishes\n- [x] **Bobby wants Recipe Rip optimized for everyone**: Sent Rex to research psychology, UI/UX, color preferences, pain points for recipe apps\n- [x] **Bobby wants Recipe Rip tested on multiple recipe sites**: Provided test URLs for Serious Eats, AllRecipes, NYT Cooking, Food Network, Bon Appétit, Epicurious, Simply Recipes, Pioneer Woman, Betty Crocker, Pillsbury, Delish, Country Living\n- [x] **AllRecipes blocked by Cloudflare**: Returns \"Just a moment...\" Cloudflare challenge page — Recipe Rip cannot bypass Cloudflare protection, shows \"This site blocked Recipe Rip\" message\n\n### In Progress\n- [ ] **Recipe Rip emoji burst animation timing**: Still iterating on how the emoji burst and recipe reveal feel — Bobby is actively testing\n\n### Blocked\n- [ ] **AllRecipes (and similar Cloudflare-protected sites)**: Cloudflare blocks Recipe Rip's proxy-based scraping. Cannot bypass without browser extension or logged-in session. Workaround: copy recipe URL from Pinterest/Facebook instead.\n\n## Key Decisions\n- **`history` ref is critical**: Must be declared as `useRef` at top of `AgentPanel()` — holds all agents' message history from localStorage, shared across renders\n- **Counter-based typing failed**: Agent sending 3 messages in one poll batch caused counter to go 1-3=-2→0 immediately\n- **Debounce approach for typing**: Timer resets on every new assistant message. Typing clears 3s after agent goes silent. Matches Telegram behavior exactly\n- **Blue pulse always shows on new message**: Removed `!focused` condition — blue pulse is independent of focus state, clears on typing or clicking\n- **Visible agents via localStorage**: Settings menu toggles agent visibility, persisted to `agent_visible` key\n- **Separate Vite entries**: `index.html` (MC router) and `agent.html` (direct AgentChatApp) avoid hash routing confusion\n- **Serve-apps.cjs multi-port**: Single server handles 3 apps on different ports with appropriate proxies\n- **git push \"Everything up-to-date\"**: This output appears when local and remote are already in sync — push succeeded\n- **Cross-device sync abandoned**: `sessions_updateMetadata` and related tools not available in gateway; sending sync messages to agent sessions caused agents to respond to them; Bobby accepted messages sync but state stays local per device\n- **iOS emoji rendering issue**: Emoji characters on iOS render with orange/brown outlines/borders as part of the system emoji font rendering. **Fix**: Canvas rendering at 2x resolution completely bypasses iOS's emoji renderer. This was the breakthrough solution.\n- **Launchd agent for auto-start**: `com.bobby.mc-all.plist` keeps `serve-apps.cjs` running and auto-restarts on crash. Replaces old vite-only launchd agents\n- **XAI key**: `xai-xMPUmMTwzAKdvKL6mNm0AkufZ9ZOoeOADhg5f9OCJtQIypMRPP1fogrhmedjLkuwSIONlm9U3jAXq5mB` works on `api.x.ai/v1/responses` (Recipe Rip)\n- **Recipe Rip in separate repo**: Excluded from main git repo (commit `37cc4b3 Exclude recipe-rip directory (separate repo)`). All changes deployed to live server, not in main git history\n- **No duplicate emojis**: Shuffled pool (`_foodPool`) populated once at startBurst, emojis drawn sequentially from shuffled pool. When pool runs out, reshuffles. `_usedFoods` Set pattern abandoned due to race condition between sync addBouncer calls\n- **stopBurst() AFTER animations**: Animations are triggered first, then `stopBurst()` is called in a setTimeout (500-600ms) so emoji elements stay in DOM during animation. Previously `stopBurst()` was called first which immediately removed all emoji elements\n- **Glass panel vs emoji z-index**: Glass panel at z-index 1002, emojis at z-index 1000. Emojis appear BEHIND the glass panel but are visible through the semi-transparent blur\n- **Demo mode for preview**: `?demo=1` URL param triggers demo mode that shows the glass panel + emoji animation without calling Grok API — saves tokens during testing\n- **Bobby wants everything \"very easy to understand\"**: Avoid jargon like \"URL\" → use \"link\"; Bobby iterates on UI details obsessively until they're right; Rex was tasked with UX psychology research\n\n## Next Steps\n1. **Tune emoji burst reveal** — Bobby is actively testing; may want timing adjustments on glass panel shrink vs emoji burst vs recipe fade-in\n2. **Implement Rex's UX research**: Skeleton loading screens, warm coral orange button (#FF6B35), empty state copy (\"Your recipes are waiting.\"), optimistic saves\n3. **Test Recipe Rip on multiple recipe sites**: Run through the test URL list Bobby has; fix extraction issues as they come up\n4. **Handle Cloudflare sites**: Show helpful message for AllRecipes/CNN-type blocks; suggest workaround (Pinterest copy-link approach)\n5. **Cross-device recipe saves**: If Bobby wants saved recipes accessible across devices, would need a backend with database (localStorage is single-device only)\n6. **Save Recipe Rip to GitHub**: It's in a separate repo that's excluded from main git. Deploy to its own GitHub repo or keep as-is on the live server only\n7. **Memory flush**: Updated `memory/2026-04-12.md` with current Recipe Rip state and key decisions\n\n## Critical Context\n- **Working URLs**: localhost:8787 (MC), localhost:8788 (Agent Chat), localhost:8789 (Recipe Rip), http://100.103.22.35:8789/ (Tailscale, Recipe Rip)\n- **Demo URL**: http://100.103.22.35:8789/?demo=1 (preview emoji animation without API call)\n- **Gateway port**: 18789 (/tools/invoke)\n- **API server port**: 3001\n- **Tailscale**: Bobby's iPhone (`100.87.202.117 iphone182`) shows as offline when not connected; must connect Tailscale app to access via Tailscale IP\n- **Key files**:\n  - `~/agent-mission-control/src/pages/AgentChatApp.tsx` — main component (~625 lines)\n  - `~/agent-mission-control/serve-apps.cjs` — multi-port server (serves all 3 apps + proxies)\n  - `~/agent-mission-control/agent.html` — Agent Chat entry point\n  - `~/agent-mission-control/server/mission-control-api.cjs` — API on port 3001\n  - `~/agent-mission-control/recipe-rip/index.html` — Recipe Rip source (single-file app, gitignored)\n  - `~/agent-mission-control/dist-recipe/index.html` — Recipe Rip production build (deployed to live server)\n  - `~/Library/LaunchAgents/com.bobby.mc-all.plist` — launchd agent for serve-apps.cjs\n  - `~/Desktop/SecondBrain/Projects/RecipeApp/PSYCHOLOGY_RESEARCH.md` — Rex's UX research\n- **LocalStorage keys**: `agent_chat_v3` (messages), `agent_last_contacted` (sorting), `agent_unread` (unread state), `agent_visible` (visible agents), `recipe_rip_v4` (saved recipes in Recipe Rip)\n- **Git**: origin/main, committed after every change. `recipe-rip/` directory is gitignored (separate repo intent)\n- **Recent commits**: `6525ffd` (scroll reset + duplicate dedupe), `e275678` (scroll to bottom on load), `5767848` (Mac panel scroll click-to-activate), `5094d8c` (iOS grid scrolling)\n- **CSS injected via `<style>` tag**: CSS from template literals in JSX is bundled into the JS file and injected at runtime\n- **Bobby's xAI key**: `xai-xMPUmMTwzAKdvKL6mNm0AkufZ9ZOoeOADhg5f9OCJtQIypMRPP1fogrhmedjLkuwSIONlm9U3jAXq5mB`\n- **Recipe Rip emoji pool**: 143 food/kitchen/culinary items managed via `_foodPool` (shuffled array) and `_foodIndex` (sequential counter). `addBouncer()` picks sequentially from shuffled pool, reshuffles when exhausted\n- **Recipe Rip animation keyframes**: `@keyframes panel-pulse`, `@keyframes emoji-burst`, `@keyframes recipe-fadein` — all in `<style>` tag in Recipe Rip HTML\n- **Recipe Rip glass panel CSS**: `.glass-panel{position:fixed;top:35%;left:50%;transform:translate(-50%,-50%);...}` with orange border (#FF6B35, 2px solid), backdrop blur, panel-pulse animation, transition for expand animation\n- **Recipe Rip emoji z-index layering**: `.eb-container` z-index 998 (emoji container, overflow:visible), `.glass-panel` z-index 1002, emoji elements z-index 1000 — emojis appear BEHIND glass panel\n- **Rex's research findings** (Recipe Rip):\n  - Colors: white/cream background, warm coral orange (#FF6B35) primary button, soft green for success\n  - UX: skeleton screens not spinners, one task per screen, 3 tabs max (Import | Saved | Settings)\n  - Speed: populate title first, then ingredients, then instructions; optimistic saves; no spinners over 2s\n  - Empty states: warm inviting language (\"Your recipes are waiting.\")\n  - Pricing tiers: Free (5extractions/5saves), $4.99/mo, $39.99/yr, $49.99 lifetime\n- **AllRecipes blocked**: Returns Cloudflare challenge page (\"Just a moment...\") — proxy cannot bypass, work around by copying recipe link from Pinterest/Facebook\n\n---\n\n**Turn Context (split turn):**\n\n\n## Original Request\nThe user is confused about something related to \"Grok\" - they expected Grok to be used but something else appears to be happening instead.\n\n## Early Progress\n- No progress yet; this appears to be the initial message of the turn.\n\n## Context for Suffix\n- The user (B G) expected Grok to be involved in whatever task or system they're working with, but the current setup is not using Grok as they anticipated.\n\n<read-files>\n/Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/skills/lobstalk/SKILL.md\n/Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/workspace-cody/MEMORY.md\n/Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/workspace-cody/memory/2026-04-05.md\n/Users/bobbygalletta/agent-mission-control/dist/agent.html\n/Users/bobbygalletta/agent-mission-control/prod-server.cjs\n/Users/bobbygalletta/agent-mission-control/src/App.tsx\n/Users/bobbygalletta/agent-mission-control/src/index.css\n/opt/homebrew/lib/node_modules/openclaw/skills/node-connect/SKILL.md\n/opt/homebrew/lib/node_modules/openclaw/skills/skill-creator/SKILL.md\n</read-files>\n\n<modified-files>\n/Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/workspace-cody/memory/2026-04-06.md\n/Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/workspace-cody/memory/2026-04-08.md\n/Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/workspace-cody/memory/2026-04-12.md\n/Users/bobbygalletta/agent-mission-control/dist/debug.html\n/Users/bobbygalletta/agent-mission-control/dist/test-module.html\n/Users/bobbygalletta/agent-mission-control/dist/test-page.html\n/Users/bobbygalletta/agent-mission-control/dist/test-react.html\n/Users/bobbygalletta/agent-mission-control/dist/test.html\n/Users/bobbygalletta/agent-mission-control/index.html\n/Users/bobbygalletta/agent-mission-control/proxy-server.js\n/Users/bobbygalletta/agent-mission-control/serve-apps.cjs\n/Users/bobbygalletta/agent-mission-control/server-https.js\n/Users/bobbygalletta/agent-mission-control/server.cjs\n/Users/bobbygalletta/agent-mission-control/server3.cjs\n/Users/bobbygalletta/agent-mission-control/src/main.tsx\n/Users/bobbygalletta/agent-mission-control/src/pages/AgentChatApp.tsx\n/Users/bobbygalletta/agent-mission-control/vite.config.ts\n/tmp/test-connect.html\n~/agent-mission-control/server-agent-chat.js\n</modified-files>",
