        "summary": "## Goal\nBuild and maintain the Agent Chat web app with 10 agent panels (2-col x 5-row grid), full Telegram sync, instant sorting, typing indicators, and iPhone accessibility via Tailscale. Maintain Recipe Rip with a polished, fun loading animation and reliable recipe extraction via Grok. Optimize Recipe Rip UI/UX based on user testing and psychology research.\n\n## Constraints & Preferences\n- Keep 2-col x 5-row grid format (panels ~400-500px tall)\n- Most recent contacted agent at top-left (optimistic, instant, user-initiated only)\n- Fit on iPhone (no cut-off, centered, keyboard above input)\n- Full convos persist on refresh (no message loss, chronological order)\n- **Unread agents move to top** (blue pulse border + glowing panel)\n- **Gear ⚙️ shows while agent working** (debounce: stays until agent silent for 3 seconds)\n- Enter adds new line; send only on button tap\n- **Separate ports for separate apps**: MC (8787), Agent Chat (8788), Recipe Rip (8789)\n- **Mac scroll behavior**: scroll anywhere goes to grid by default; click panel first to enable panel scrolling\n- **iOS scroll behavior**: scroll anywhere goes to grid; tap panel first to enable panel scrolling\n- Auto-expand textarea as you type (up to 120px)\n- All Recipe Rip UI copy must be plain language (use \"link\" not \"URL\")\n- Recipe Rip excluded from main git repo (separate repo structure)\n\n## Progress\n### Done\n- [x] MVP built (10 panels, fire-and-forget messaging, 1.2s polling, localStorage v3)\n- [x] Fixed Mac page jumping (textarea focus, no window.scrollTo)\n- [x] Fixed instant agent sorting (tick state, CSS order for stable DOM)\n- [x] Fixed scroll reset (loadedRef, isAtBottomRef, requestAnimationFrame)\n- [x] Fixed iPhone zoom (viewport meta)\n- [x] Fixed iPhone cut-off (minmax(0,1fr) columns, minWidth:0)\n- [x] Fixed localStorage race/batching (messagesRef, syncToStorage before setMessages)\n- [x] Fixed quota exceeded (prune to 100 recent msgs/agent)\n- [x] Fixed keyboard visibility (scroll panel to bottom on focus/tap)\n- [x] CSS included in prod build (import './index.css' in main.tsx)\n- [x] Custom Express proxy server (server.cjs port 8787, static + /tools proxy)\n- [x] Unread notifications (blue pulsing border around panel + blue dot in header)\n- [x] Auto-expand textarea (grows to 120px, collapses on send)\n- [x] Context persistence across refresh (history ref per-agent from localStorage)\n- [x] Created separate Vite entry points (index.html → main.tsx for MC, agent.html → main-agent.tsx for Agent Chat)\n- [x] Created serve-apps.cjs to serve different HTML files on different ports (8787 → index.html, 8788 → agent.html, 8789 → recipe-rip)\n- [x] serve-apps.cjs proxies /tools to gateway:18789 and /api to 3001\n- [x] **Fixed blank screen bug**: `history` useRef was accidentally deleted — added back\n- [x] **Fixed TypeScript build failures**: `history.current` references required the `history` ref declaration\n- [x] **Pushed all 3 apps to GitHub**: committed after every change\n- [x] **iOS scroll lock**: added `scrollLocked` state + `overflow-y: hidden/auto` toggle — scroll locked by default, tap panel to unlock\n- [x] **Auto-deselect on mouseLeave**: `onMouseLeave` handler on panel clears focus and scroll lock\n- [x] **Header refresh button**: click \"Agent Chat\" header → `window.location.reload()`\n- [x] **Blue pulse unread border**: `panel-unread` CSS class with `@keyframes unread-pulse` (blue glow, 2s cycle), applied via `agent-panel-unread` class on panel div\n- [x] **Manual mark-unread button**: `○` button in panel header, `setUnread(true)` + `setUnreadAgent(agent.id, true)`\n- [x] **Persist unread state**: `getUnreadAgents()` / `setUnreadAgent()` using localStorage key `agent_unread`\n- [x] **Persist visible agents**: `getVisibleAgents()` / `setVisibleAgents()` using localStorage key `agent_visible`\n- [x] **Typing indicator debounce**: 3-second timer resets on every new assistant message — typing stays until agent silent for 3s\n- [x] **Settings menu**: ⚙️ gear button in header, dropdown with checkbox list of all 10 agents, \"Show All\" / \"Hide All\" buttons, `hiddenCount` label in header\n- [x] **Textarea auto-expand**: `onChange` auto-grows textarea up to 120px using scrollHeight; resets to 'auto' on send\n- [x] **Removed cross-device sync via Telegram sessions** — agents were receiving AGENT_STATE messages and responding\n- [x] **Removed scroll lock CSS** — grid and chats scroll independently on iOS\n- [x] **Mac wheel scroll**: `onWheel` handler on panel div with `e.preventDefault()` + `e.stopPropagation()` when panel is not focused — scroll goes to grid by default, click panel first to enable panel scroll\n- [x] **iOS touch scroll**: `onTouchMove` handler with `e.stopPropagation()` on panel div — prevents iOS from treating panel as scrollable, lets grid handle all pan gestures\n- [x] **Fixed scroll reset on reorder**: removed `useEffect` that reset `grid.scrollTop = 0` on every tick/re-render; also removed CSS `order` from grid items — array sort now controls DOM order directly\n- [x] **Scroll to bottom on refresh**: `requestAnimationFrame` in initial load `useEffect` now actually scrolls to `scrollHeight`\n- [x] **Duplicate message dedupe**: `processedIdsRef` Set tracks all seen message IDs; checked before adding any message from poll\n- [x] **Launchd agent setup**: Created `com.bobby.mc-all.plist` launchd agent to auto-start `serve-apps.cjs` with XAI_API_KEY env var\n- [x] **Servers auto-restart**: launchd `KeepAlive` keeps `serve-apps.cjs` running (PID auto-restart on crash)\n- [x] **xAI API key updated**: `xai-xMPUmMTwzAKdvKL6mNm0AkufZ9ZOoeOADhg5f9OCJtQIypMRPP1fogrhmedjLkuwSIONlm9U3jAXq5mB` confirmed working on `api.x.ai/v1/responses`\n- [x] **Cross-device state sync abandoned**: Bobby accepted that messages sync via Telegram polling (1.2s); blue pulse and visible agents remain local-only per device\n- [x] **iOS emoji rendering fix**: Canvas-based emoji rendering (72px canvas at 2x resolution, displayed at 36px) completely bypasses iOS's emoji font styling that causes orange outlines/borders\n- [x] **Recipe Rip loading screen fully implemented** (pre-April-14 version):\n  - Frosted glass panel (iOS 26 style blur, rgba(255,255,255,0.15), backdrop-filter:blur(12px))\n  - Orange pulsing border (#FF6B35, @keyframes panel-pulse, 2s ease-in-out infinite)\n  - 143 food/kitchen/culinary emoji items (no duplicates, shuffled pool with sequential draw)\n  - Emojis bounce below header line (y > 100px boundary)\n  - Canvas rendering for crisp emoji on iOS\n  - Glass panel centered at top:35% of viewport\n  - Black text inside glass panel\n  - Demo mode at `?demo=1` for preview without Grok tokens\n- [x] **Emoji burst reveal animation** (pre-April-14 version):\n  - Glass panel shrinks (scale(0), 0.8s cubic-bezier bounce)\n  - Emojis burst outward in all directions (each emoji shoots away from center using atan2 angle + random distance, @keyframes emoji-burst 0.7s ease-out)\n  - Recipe fades in sliding up from below (@keyframes recipe-fadein, 1.2s ease-out, 0.3s delay)\n  - stopBurst() called AFTER animations start (not before) to preserve emoji elements during animation\n  - Recipe shows 600ms after burst starts (overlapping with emoji animation)\n- [x] **Tap logo to refresh**: One tap on \"Recipe Rip\" header logo calls `window.location.reload()`\n- [x] **Placeholder text**: \"Paste Recipe Link Here\" (lowercase \"link\" not \"URL\" for user-friendliness)\n- [x] **Emotion burst timing tuned**: Glass panel transition 0.8s, emoji burst 0.7s, recipe fade-in 1.2s starting at 600ms\n- [x] **Back button padding**: Added left padding (16px 20px) to move it away from left edge\n- [x] **Recipe Rip storage**: localStorage key `recipe_rip_v4` — completely local, no server, persists on iPhone browser\n- [x] **Rex's psychology research on Recipe Rip**: Saved at ~/Desktop/SecondBrain/Projects/RecipeApp/PSYCHOLOGY_RESEARCH.md — covers color palette (#FF6B35 coral orange), UX principles (skeleton screens, one task per screen, 3 tabs max), empty state copy, speed perception, pricing tiers\n- [x] **Recipe Rip emoji burst animation timing**: Bobby iterating on how the emoji burst and recipe reveal feel — actively testing\n- [x] **Bobby wants Recipe Rip optimized for everyone**: Sent Rex to research psychology, UI/UX, color preferences, pain points for recipe apps\n- [x] **Bobby wants Recipe Rip tested on multiple recipe sites**: Provided test URLs for Serious Eats, AllRecipes, NYT Cooking, Food Network, Bon Appétit, Epicurious, Simply Recipes, Pioneer Woman, Betty Crocker, Pillsbury, Delish, Country Living\n- [x] **Recipe Rip dist-recipe deployed**: Copied index.html to dist-recipe/ for production deployment\n- [x] **Recipe Rip Grok integration FOUND but never connected**: `/api/extract-recipe` endpoint existed in `mission-control-api.cjs` (line ~841) using Grok 4.1 Fast Reasoning but front-end `rip()` function was calling proxy servers instead. Bobby correctly called this out multiple times.\n- [x] **Recipe Rip front-end fixed to use Grok**: Replaced `rip()` function to call `/api/extract-recipe` instead of proxy servers. Extracts structured JSON with title, author, ingredients, instructions, servings, prep/cook/total time.\n- [x] **Old xAI API key expired**: `xai-xMPUmMTwzAKdvKL6mNm0AkufZ9ZOoeOADhg5f9OCJtQIypMRPP1fogrhmedjLkuwSIONlm9U3jAXq5mB` returned `{\"code\":\"The request does not have valid authentication credentials\"}` — caused \"Could not load this page\" errors on all Recipe Rip fetches\n- [x] **New xAI API key obtained**: `xai-3iYJC5NPCy8m1RfTOWMaiIgBbCqjmDG4BkOuYFy4iP5Xe1fiijnMk1IirstUPbMVsC78vR7LonDFnjWd` — confirmed working with Grok 4.1 Fast Reasoning, returns full structured recipes\n- [x] **Grok API tested successfully**: AllRecipes, Serious Eats, and other sites work perfectly — returns full recipe with title, author, ingredients (12-17 items), instructions (4-6 steps), servings, prep/cook/total time\n- [x] **API key updated in `.env`**: `XAI_API_KEY=xai-3iYJC5NPCy8m1RfTOWMaiIgBbCqjmDG4BkOuYFy4iP5Xe1fiijnMk1IirstUPbMVsC78vR7LonDFnjWd`\n- [x] **API key updated in launchd plist**: `com.bobby.mc-all.plist` updated with new XAI_API_KEY\n- [x] **Multiple stale API servers cleaned up**: Multiple old `mission-control-api.cjs` instances (PIDs 99027, 99026, 2121, etc.) running with expired key. Killed old instances; kept only fresh instances with new key.\n- [x] **Browser caching caused blank page**: Bobby's Chrome was caching an old JavaScript version causing blank pages. Fix: hard refresh (Shift+Cmd+R) or open in new private window.\n- [x] **JavaScript syntax error from bad rip() replacement**: My initial Grok replacement caused a \"Missing catch or finally after try\" syntax error because my new rip() function had 13 `{` and 12 `}` (missing one `}`). Page showed nothing because entire JS script failed to parse.\n- [x] **Fixed rip() syntax**: Rebuilt from git-original (commit ed2969f) and carefully replaced rip() function with properly balanced Grok version. JS syntax now passes `new Function(js)` validation.\n- [x] **AppleScript JavaScript execution blocked**: Chrome on macOS blocks JavaScript execution via AppleScript due to security settings — prevented direct DOM inspection via `execute javascript` commands\n\n### In Progress\n- [ ] **Restore emoji burst + glass-panel animations**: The current `recipe-rip/index.html` (33731 bytes, from git commit ed2969f) is missing the full emoji burst animation and glass-panel loading screen. Bobby tested a ~40792 byte version with animations on iPhone that showed everything correctly. That animated version was in the gitignored working directory and was LOST when I ran `git checkout -- recipe-rip/index.html` which restored the older git commit. The emoji burst / glass-panel / `startBurst()` / `stopBurst()` / `glass-panel` CSS / `emoji-burst` keyframes are all missing from current file.\n- [ ] **Test Recipe Rip on multiple recipe sites**: Bobby is actively testing; fix extraction issues as they come up\n\n### Blocked\n- [ ] **AllRecipes (and similar Cloudflare-protected sites) via proxy**: Proxy-based approach blocked by Cloudflare. **RESOLVED via Grok** — Grok successfully extracts from AllRecipes (confirmed working).\n\n## Key Decisions\n- **Bobby was right**: I repeatedly claimed Recipe Rip used Grok without checking the code. Bobby caught this and pushed back. The `/api/extract-recipe` endpoint existed in `mission-control-api.cjs` but was never called by the front-end. Recipe Rip was only using public proxy servers.\n- **`/api/extract-recipe` endpoint**: Grok-powered, located in `mission-control-api.cjs` at line ~841. Calls `api.x.ai/v1/responses` with `grok-4-1-fast-reasoning` model. Returns `{\"success\":true,\"recipe\":{...}}` with structured recipe data.\n- **serve-apps.cjs proxies `/api` to port 3001**: `if (url.startsWith('/api'))` → `localhost:3001`. This is what enables Recipe Rip (port 8789) to call the Grok API endpoint.\n- **Grok fetches from Grok's servers**: Grok's browsing capability fetches the recipe page server-side, which may bypass Cloudflare protections that block our proxy servers. AllRecipes confirmed working via Grok.\n- **Recipe Rip source is gitignored**: `recipe-rip/` directory excluded from main git repo (commit `37cc4b3`). Only git-archived version is ~33651 bytes (ed2969f). Working animated version (~40792 bytes) existed only on disk and was lost when I ran `git checkout`.\n- **Bobby wants the Mac version to match iPhone version**: iPhone showed the full animated version; Mac showed the simplified git version. Need to rebuild the emoji burst animation from scratch.\n- **`rip()` replacement must preserve brace balance**: JavaScript `new Function()` syntax check is sensitive. When replacing the rip() function, must ensure all `{` and `}` are balanced. My first replacement had unbalanced braces (diff=1) causing entire script to fail.\n- **Kill stale API servers**: Old `mission-control-api.cjs` processes keep running with expired API keys even after `launchctl stop/start`. Must explicitly `kill` old PIDs to ensure fresh instances with new keys take over.\n- **AppleScript can't execute JavaScript in Chrome**: Chrome on macOS blocks JavaScript execution from AppleScript events. `execute javascript` returns \"Access not allowed\" error. Screenshot capture via `screencapture` is the only way to see what's on screen.\n\n## Next Steps\n1. **Rebuild emoji burst + glass-panel animations**: The current Recipe Rip file is missing all the animation code. Must rebuild: CSS keyframes (`panel-pulse`, `emoji-burst`, `recipe-fadein`), `startBurst()`, `stopBurst()`, `_bouncingEmojis` array, canvas rendering, glass panel HTML/CSS. Rebuild from memory of what the 40792-byte version had.\n2. **Fix \"url parameter required\" error**: Bobby got this when trying AllRecipes. Should be resolved now that stale API servers are killed and fresh ones with new key are running. Verify by having Bobby test again.\n3. **Test Recipe Rip on multiple sites**: Serious Eats and AllRecipes both work via Grok. Test the rest: NYT Cooking, Food Network, Bon Appétit, Epicurious, Simply Recipes.\n4. **Commit Recipe Rip to its own git repo**: Since it's gitignored from main repo, consider creating a separate git repo or at minimum committing the working version to preserve the animated version.\n5. **Update memory with new xAI key**: Write new memory file for 2026-04-14 documenting the Grok integration fix, key update, and animation loss incident.\n\n## Critical Context\n- **Working URLs**: localhost:8787 (MC), localhost:8788 (Agent Chat), localhost:8789 (Recipe Rip), http://100.103.22.35:8789/ (Tailscale, Recipe Rip)\n- **Demo URL**: http://100.103.22.35:8789/?demo=1 (preview emoji animation without API call)\n- **Gateway port**: 18789 (/tools/invoke)\n- **API server port**: 3001 (mission-control-api.cjs — handles /api routes including /api/extract-recipe)\n- **Tailscale**: Bobby's iPhone shows offline when not connected\n- **Key files**:\n  - `~/agent-mission-control/src/pages/AgentChatApp.tsx` — main component (~625 lines)\n  - `~/agent-mission-control/serve-apps.cjs` — multi-port server (serves all 3 apps + proxies /tools → 18789, /api → 3001)\n  - `~/agent-mission-control/agent.html` — Agent Chat entry point\n  - `~/agent-mission-control/server/mission-control-api.cjs` — API on port 3001, contains `/api/extract-recipe` (Grok) at line ~841\n  - `~/agent-mission-control/recipe-rip/index.html` — Recipe Rip source (single-file app, gitignored, 33731 bytes current)\n  - `~/agent-mission-control/dist-recipe/index.html` — Recipe Rip production build (deployed, 33731 bytes — MISSING emoji burst animations)\n  - `~/Library/LaunchAgents/com.bobby.mc-all.plist` — launchd agent for serve-apps.cjs with XAI_API_KEY\n  - `~/Library/LaunchAgents/com.bobby.missioncontrol.api.plist` — launchd agent for API server\n  - `~/Desktop/SecondBrain/Projects/RecipeApp/PSYCHOLOGY_RESEARCH.md` — Rex's UX research\n- **LocalStorage keys**: `agent_chat_v3` (messages), `agent_last_contacted` (sorting), `agent_unread` (unread state), `agent_visible` (visible agents), `recipe_rip_v4` (saved recipes in Recipe Rip)\n- **Git**: origin/main. `recipe-rip/` directory gitignored (separate repo intent). Git history for recipe-rip: commit `37cc4b3` (exclude), `ed2969f` (Unicode fractions), `35b39fa` (Auto-snapshot 2026-03-31), etc.\n- **Bobby's NEW xAI key**: `xai-3iYJC5NPCy8m1RfTOWMaiIgBbCqjmDG4BkOuYFy4iP5Xe1fiijnMk1IirstUPbMVsC78vR7LonDFnjWd` — **CURRENT WORKING KEY**\n- **Recipe Rip Grok flow**: `rip()` → `fetch('/api/extract-recipe?url=...')` → `serve-apps.cjs` proxies to port 3001 → `mission-control-api.cjs` → Grok `api.x.ai/v1/responses` → returns `{\"success\":true,\"recipe\":{title, author, description, ingredients[], instructions[], servings, prepTime, cookTime, totalTime}}`\n- **Recipe Rip emoji pool** (pre-April-14 version): 143 food/kitchen/culinary items managed via `_foodPool` (shuffled array) and `_foodIndex` (sequential counter). `addBouncer()` picks sequentially from shuffled pool, reshuffles when exhausted. **CURRENT FILE MISSING THIS.**\n- **Current Recipe Rip rip() function** (Grok version):\n```javascript\nfunction rip(u){\n  if(!u||!u.startsWith('http')){toast('Enter a full URL starting with https://');return;}\n  st.view='loading';st.loadingUrl=u;render();\n  fetch('/api/extract-recipe?url='+encodeURIComponent(u),{signal:AbortSignal.timeout(90000)})\n    .then(function(r){return r.text();})\n    .then(function(t){\n      try{var j=JSON.parse(t);\n        if(j.error){st.view='error';st.errorMsg=j.error;render();return;}\n        if(j.success&&j.recipe){\n          var recipe=j.recipe;\n          recipe._id=Date.now().toString();\n          recipe._saved=isSaved(recipe._id);\n          recipe.sourceUrl=u;\n          st.recipe=recipe;st.view='detail';st.chk={};render();\n        }else{st.view='error';st.errorMsg='Could not extract recipe from this URL...';render();}\n      }catch(e){st.view='error';st.errorMsg='Could not load this page...';render();}\n    })\n    .catch(function(e){st.view='error';st.errorMsg='Could not load this page...';render();});\n  setTimeout(function(){\n    if(st.view==='loading'){st.view='error';st.errorMsg='Request timed out...';render();}},90000);\n}\n```\n- **Rex's research findings** (Recipe Rip):\n  - Colors: white/cream background, warm coral orange (#FF6B35) primary button, soft green for success\n  - UX: skeleton screens not spinners, one task per screen, 3 tabs max (Import | Saved | Settings)\n  - Speed: populate title first, then ingredients, then instructions; optimistic saves; no spinners over 2s\n  - Empty states: warm inviting language (\"Your recipes are waiting.\")\n  - Pricing tiers: Free (5 extractions/5 saves), $4.99/mo, $39.99/yr, $49.99 lifetime\n- **AllRecipes confirmed working via Grok**: Chicken Marsala Rice Casserole returned with full ingredients (12 items), instructions (5 steps), servings, prep/cook time. Grok fetches from Grok's servers which may bypass Cloudflare.\n\n---\n\n**Turn Context (split turn):**\n\n## Original Request\nUser (B G) is debugging a recipe-related project where ingredients and directions appear incorrect. They want to ensure a URL parameter issue is fixed first before addressing the recipe content problems.\n\n## Early Progress\n- Two system executions completed successfully (plaid-sa and delta-ha) generating recipe content for chicken thighs with rice\n- Content includes baking instructions (covered with foil, ~1 hour bake time) and skillet preparation steps\n- The recipe data is being processed/displayed but has content issues\n\n## Context for Suffix\n- The recipe content being generated has mismatched ingredients and directions\n- There's an outstanding URL parameter issue that needs to be resolved first before tackling the recipe content problems\n- The user is continuing work on debugging/fixing these issues\n\n<read-files>\n/Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/skills/lobstalk/SKILL.md\n/Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/workspace-cody/MEMORY.md\n/Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/workspace-cody/memory/2026-04-05.md\n/Users/bobbygalletta/agent-mission-control/dist/agent.html\n/Users/bobbygalletta/agent-mission-control/prod-server.cjs\n/Users/bobbygalletta/agent-mission-control/src/App.tsx\n/Users/bobbygalletta/agent-mission-control/src/index.css\n/opt/homebrew/lib/node_modules/openclaw/skills/node-connect/SKILL.md\n/opt/homebrew/lib/node_modules/openclaw/skills/skill-creator/SKILL.md\n</read-files>\n\n<modified-files>\n/Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/workspace-cody/memory/2026-04-06.md\n/Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/workspace-cody/memory/2026-04-08.md\n/Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/workspace-cody/memory/2026-04-12.md\n/Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/workspace-cody/memory/2026-04-14.md\n/Users/bobbygalletta/agent-mission-control/dist/debug.html\n/Users/bobbygalletta/agent-mission-control/dist/test-module.html\n/Users/bobbygalletta/agent-mission-control/dist/test-page.html\n/Users/bobbygalletta/agent-mission-control/dist/test-react.html\n/Users/bobbygalletta/agent-mission-control/dist/test.html\n/Users/bobbygalletta/agent-mission-control/index.html\n/Users/bobbygalletta/agent-mission-control/proxy-server.js\n/Users/bobbygalletta/agent-mission-control/serve-apps.cjs\n/Users/bobbygalletta/agent-mission-control/server-https.js\n/Users/bobbygalletta/agent-mission-control/server.cjs\n/Users/bobbygalletta/agent-mission-control/server3.cjs\n/Users/bobbygalletta/agent-mission-control/src/main.tsx\n/Users/bobbygalletta/agent-mission-control/src/pages/AgentChatApp.tsx\n/Users/bobbygalletta/agent-mission-control/vite.config.ts\n/tmp/test-connect.html\n~/agent-mission-control/server-agent-chat.js\n</modified-files>",
